Name: Tri-Horned Dragon
Text: An unworthy dragon with three sharp horns sprouting from its head.

Name: Blue-Eyes White Dragon
Text: This legendary dragon is a powerful engine of destruction. Virtually invincible, very few have faced this awesome creature and lived to tell the tale.

Name: Hitotsu-Me Giant
Text: Capable of firing cannonballs from its mouth for long-range attacks, this creature is particularly effective in mountain battles.

Name: Flame Swordsman
Text: Flame Manipulator + "Masaki the Legendary Swordsman"

Name: Skull Servant
Text: A skeletal ghost that isn't strong but can mean trouble in large numbers.

Name: Dark Magician
Text: The ultimate wizard in terms of attack and defense.

Name: Gaia The Fierce Knight
Text: A knight whose horse travels faster than the wind. His battle-charge is a force to be reckoned with.

Name: Celtic Guardian
Text: An elf who learned to wield a sword, he baffles enemies with lightning-swift attacks.

Name: Basic Insect
Text: Usually found traveling in swarms, this creature's ideal environment is the forest.

Name: Mammoth Graveyard
Text: A mammoth that protects the graves of its pack and is absolutely merciless when facing grave-robbers.

Name: Silver Fang
Text: A snow wolf that's beautiful to the eye, but absolutely vicious in battle.

Name: Dark Gray
Text: Entirely gray, this beast has rarely been seen by mortal eyes.

Name: Trial of Nightmare
Text: This fiend passes judgment on enemies that are locked in coffins.

Name: Nemuriko
Text: A child-like creature that controls a sleep fiend to beckon enemies into eternal slumber.

Name: The 13th Grave
Text: A zombie that suddenly appeared from plot #13 - an empty grave.

Name: Charubin the Fire Knight
Text: Monster Egg + "Hinotama Soul"

Name: Flame Manipulator
Text: This Spellcaster attacks enemies with fire-related spells such as "Sea of Flames" and "Wall of Fire".

Name: Monster Egg
Text: A warrior hidden within an egg that attacks enemies by flinging eggshells.

Name: Firegrass
Text: A fire-breathing plant found growing near volcanoes.

Name: Darkfire Dragon
Text: Firegrass + "Petit Dragon"

Name: Dark King of the Abyss
Text: It's said that this King of the Netherworld once had the power to rule over the dark.

Name: Fiend Reflection #2
Text: A bird-beast that summons reinforcements with a hand mirror.

Name: Fusionist
Text: Petit Angel + "Mystical Sheep #2"

Name: Turtle Tiger
Text: A tiger encased in a protective shell that attacks with razor-sharp fangs.

Name: Petit Dragon
Text: A very small dragon known for its vicious attacks.

Name: Petit Angel
Text: A quick-moving and tiny fairy that's very difficult to hit.

Name: Hinotama Soul
Text: An intensely hot flame creature that rams anything standing in its way.

Name: Aqua Madoor
Text: A wizard of the waters that conjures a liquid wall to crush any enemies that oppose him.

Name: Kagemusha of the Blue Flame
Text: Serving as a double for the Ruler of the Blue Flame, he's a master swordsman that wields a fine blade.

Name: Flame Ghost
Text: Skull Servant + "Dissolverock"

Name: Two-Mouth Darkruler
Text: A dinosaur with two deadly jaws, it stores electricity in its horn and releases high voltage bolts from the mouth on its back.

Name: Dissolverock
Text: A monster born in the lava pits, it generates intense heat that can melt away its enemies.

Name: Root Water
Text: An amphibian capable of calling up a massive tidal wave from the dark seas to wipe out enemy monsters.

Name: The Furious Sea King
Text: Grand King of the Seven Seas, he's able to summon massive tidal waves to drown the enemy.

Name: Green Phantom King
Text: This youthful king of the forests lives in a green world, abundant with trees and wildlife.

Name: Ray & Temperature
Text: The Sun and the North Wind join hands to deliver a devastating combination of heat and gale-force winds.

Name: King Fog
Text: A fiend that dwells in a blinding curtain of smoke.

Name: Mystical Sheep #2
Text: A monstrous sheep with a long tail for hypnotizing enemies.

Name: Masaki the Legendary Swordsman
Text: Legendary swordmaster Masaki is a veteran of over 100 battles.

Name: Kurama
Text: A vicious bird that attacks from the skies with its whip-like tail.

Name: Legendary Sword
Text: Equip only to a Warrior monster. It gains 300 ATK/DEF.

Name: Beast Fangs
Text: A Beast-Type monster equipped with this card increases its ATK and DEF by 300 points.

Name: Violet Crystal
Text: (This card is not treated as a "Crystal" card.) Equip only to a Zombie monster. It gains 300 ATK/DEF

Name: Book of Secret Arts
Text: A Spellcaster-Type monster equipped with this card increases its ATK and DEF by 300 points.

Name: Power of Kaishin
Text: Equip only to an Aqua monster. It gains 300 ATK/DEF.

Name: Dragon Capture Jar
Text: Change all face-up Dragon-Type monsters on the field to Defense Position, also they cannot change their battle positions.

Name: Forest
Text: All Insect, Beast, Plant, and Beast-Warrior monsters on the field gain 200 ATK/DEF.

Name: Wasteland
Text: All Dinosaur, Zombie, and Rock monsters on the field gain 200 ATK/DEF.

Name: Mountain
Text: All Dragon, Winged Beast, and Thunder monsters on the field gain 200 ATK/DEF.

Name: Sogen
Text: All Warrior and Beast-Warrior monsters on the field gain 200 ATK/DEF.

Name: Umi
Text: All Fish, Sea Serpent, Thunder, and Aqua monsters on the field gain 200 ATK/DEF, also all Machine and Pyro monsters on the field lose 200 ATK/DEF.

Name: Yami
Text: All Fiend and Spellcaster monsters on the field gain 200 ATK/DEF, also all Fairy monsters on the field lose 200 ATK/DEF.

Name: Dark Hole
Text: Destroy all monsters on the field.

Name: Raigeki
Text: Destroy all monsters your opponent controls.

Name: Red Medicine
Text: Increase your Life Points by 500 points.

Name: Sparks
Text: Inflict 200 points of damage to your opponent's Life Points.

Name: Hinotama Soul
Text: Inflict 500 damage to your opponent.

Name: Fissure
Text: Destroy the 1 face-up monster your opponent controls that has the lowest ATK (your choice, if tied).

Name: Trap Hole
Text: When your opponent Normal or Flip Summons 1 monster with 1000 or more ATK: Target that monster; destroy that target.

Name: Polymerization
Text: Fusion Summon 1 Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck, using monsters from your hand or field as Fusion Material.

Name: Remove Trap
Text: Select 1 face-up Trap Card on the field and destroy it.

Name: Two-Pronged Attack
Text: Select and destroy 2 of your monsters and 1 of your opponent's monsters.

Name: Mystical Elf
Text: A delicate elf that lacks offense, but has a terrific defense backed by mystical power.

Name: Tyhone
Text: Capable of firing cannonballs from its mouth for long-range attacks, this creature is particularly effective in mountain battles.

Name: Beaver Warrior
Text: What this creature lacks in size it makes up for in defense when battling in the prairie.

Name: Gravedigger Ghoul
Text: Select up to 2 Monster Card(s) from your opponent's Graveyard. Remove the selected card(s) from play.

Name: Curse of Dragon
Text: A wicked dragon that taps into dark forces to execute a powerful attack.

Name: Karbonala Warrior
Text: M-Warrior #1 + "M-Warrior #2"

Name: Giant Soldier of Stone
Text: A giant warrior made of stone. A punch from this creature has earth-shaking results.

Name: Uraby
Text: Fast on its feet, this dinosaur rips enemies to shreds with its sharp claws.

Name: Red-Eyes Black Dragon
Text: A ferocious dragon with a deadly attack.

Name: Reaper of the Cards
Text: FLIP: Select 1 Trap Card on the field and destroy it. If the selected card is Set, pick up and see the card. If it is a Trap Card, it is destroyed. If it is a Spell Card, return it to its original position.

Name: Witty Phantom
Text: Dressed in a night-black tuxedo, this creature presides over the darkness.

Name: Larvas
Text: A fast-moving, bird-like creature that strangles opposing monsters with its long, thin arms.

Name: Hard Armor
Text: A living suit of armor that attacks enemies with a bone-jarring tackle.

Name: Man Eater
Text: Man-eating plant with poison feelers for attacking enemies.

Name: M-Warrior #1
Text: Specializing in combination attacks, this warrior uses magnetism to block an enemy's escape.

Name: M-Warrior #2
Text: Specializing in combination attacks, this warrior is equipped with a tough, magnetically coated armor.

Name: Spirit of the Harp
Text: A spirit that soothes the soul with the music of its heavenly harp.

Name: Armaill
Text: A strange warrior who manipulates three deadly blades with both hands and his tail.

Name: Terra the Terrible
Text: Known as a swamp dweller, this creature is a minion of the dark forces.

Name: Frenzied Panda
Text: A savage beast that carries a big bamboo stick for beating down its enemies.

Name: Kumootoko
Text: A massive, intelligent spider that traps enemies with webbing.

Name: Meda Bat
Text: An eyeball fiend created by a servant of the wicked, it uses "Dark Blasts" to blow away its enemies.

Name: Enchanting Mermaid
Text: A beautiful mermaid that lures voyagers to a watery grave.

Name: Fireyarou
Text: A malevolent creature wrapped in flames that attacks enemies with intense fire.

Name: Dragoness the Wicked Knight
Text: Armaill + "One-Eyed Shield Dragon"

Name: One-Eyed Shield Dragon
Text: This dragon wears a shield not only for its own protection, but also for ramming its enemies.

Name: Dark Energy
Text: Increase the ATK and DEF of a Fiend-Type monster equipped with this card by 300 points.

Name: Laser Cannon Armor
Text: An Insect-Type monster equipped with this card increases its ATK and DEF by 300 points.

Name: Vile Germs
Text: A Plant-Type monster equipped with this card increases its ATK and DEF by 300 points.

Name: Silver Bow and Arrow
Text: A Fairy-Type monster equipped with this card increases its ATK and DEF by 300 points.

Name: Dragon Treasure
Text: A Dragon-Type monster equipped with this card increases its ATK and DEF by 300 points.

Name: Electro-Whip
Text: Increase the ATK and DEF of a Thunder-Type monster equipped with this card by 300 points.

Name: Mystical Moon
Text: Equip only to a Beast-Warrior-Type monster. It gains 300 ATK and DEF.

Name: Stop Defense
Text: Select 1 Defense Position monster on your opponent's side of the field and change it to Attack Position.

Name: Machine Conversion Factory
Text: A Machine-Type monster equipped with this card increases its ATK and DEF by 300 points.

Name: Raise Body Heat
Text: A Dinosaur-Type monster equipped with this card increases its ATK and DEF by 300 points.

Name: Follow Wind
Text: ncrease the ATK and DEF of a Winged-Beast-Type monster equipped with this card by 300 points.

Name: Goblin's Secret Remedy
Text: Increase your Life Points by 600 points.

Name: Final Flame
Text: Inflict 600 points of damage to your opponent's Life Points.

Name: Swords of Revealing Light
Text: After this card's activation, it remains on the field, but destroy it during the End Phase of your opponent's 3rd turn. When this card is activated: If your opponent controls a face-down monster, flip all monsters they control face-up. While this card is face-up on the field, your opponent's monsters cannot declare an attack.

Name: Metal Dragon
Text: Steel Ogre Grotto #1 + "Lesser Dragon"

Name: Spike Seadra
Text: Using the spikes sprouting from its body, this creature stabs its opponents and floods them with electricity.

Name: Tripwire Beast
Text: This creature attacks with electromagnetic waves.

Name: Skull Red Bird
Text: This monster swoops down and attacks with a rain of knives stored in its wings.

Name: Armed Ninja
Text: FLIP: Target 1 Spell Card on the field; destroy that target. (If the target is Set, reveal it, and destroy it if it is a Spell Card. Otherwise, return it to its original position.)

Name: Flower Wolf
Text: Silver Fang + "Darkworld Thorns"

Name: Man-Eater Bug
Text: FLIP: Target 1 monster on the field; destroy that target.

Name: Sand Stone
Text: Appears from underground and attacks with long, snake-like tentacles.

Name: Hane-Hane
Text: FLIP: Select 1 monster on the field and return it to its owner's hand.

Name: Misairuzame
Text: A missile-launching fish protected by deadly spikes.

Name: Steel Ogre Grotto #1
Text: A steel idol worshipped in the Land of Machines.

Name: Lesser Dragon
Text: A minor dragon incapable of breathing fire.

Name: Darkworld Thorns
Text: A thorny plant found in the darklands that wraps itself around any unwary traveler.

Name: Drooling Lizard
Text: A blood-sucking snake in human form that attacks any living being that passes nearby.

Name: Armored Starfish
Text: A bluish starfish with a solid hide capable of fending off attacks.

Name: Succubus Knight
Text: A warrior wizard adept in casting bone-chilling spells.

Name: Monster Reborn
Text: Target 1 monster in either GY; Special Summon it.

Name: Pot of Greed
Text: Draw 2 cards.

Name: Right Leg of the Forbidden One
Text: A forbidden right leg sealed by magic. Whosoever breaks this seal will know infinite power.

Name: Left Leg of the Forbidden One
Text: A forbidden left leg sealed by magic. Whosoever breaks this seal will know infinite power.

Name: Right Arm of the Forbidden One
Text: A forbidden right arm sealed by magic. Whosoever breaks this seal will know infinite power.

Name: Left Arm of the Forbidden One
Text: A forbidden left arm sealed by magic. Whosoever breaks this seal will know infinite power.

Name: Exodia the Forbidden One
Text: If you have "Right Leg of the Forbidden One", "Left Leg of the Forbidden One", "Right Arm of the Forbidden One" and "Left Arm of the Forbidden One" in addition to this card in your hand, you win the Duel.

Name: Gaia the Dragon Champion
Text: Gaia The Fierce Knight + "Curse of Dragon"
